-- Mauritius Government Domestic Debt Increased 0.4% in November, Bank Says
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2010-12-28T05:58:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/mauritius-government-domestic-debt-increased-0-4-in-november-bank-says.html
Mauritius’ central government
domestic debt increased by 0.4 percent in November, the central
bank said in a statement published on its website yesterday.  Domestic debt grew to 125.50 billion rupees from 125.05
billion rupees, it said.  The central government’s short term obligations rose to
51.04 billion rupees in November from 50.61 billion rupees a
month earlier, the statistics division of the central bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
